A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Charles Tamlin Hall Jr.; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Charles Tamlin Hall Jr. on January 20, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Charles Tamlin Hall Jr. was born on July 10, 1950, a beloved son of Tamlin and
5 Mary Nell Hall; and
6 WHEREAS, a proud alumnus of the University of Georgia (UGA), he was a lifelong fan of
7 the Georgia Bulldogs and served as President of the UGA College of Agricultural and
8 Environmental Sciences Alumni Association Board of Directors; and
9 WHEREAS, he further served as Founder and President/CEO of Association Services Group
10 (ASG) of LaGrange, Georgia, from 1995 to 2021, which was recognized many times as one
11 of the fastest growing companies in Georgia; and
12 WHEREAS, a man of deep and abiding faith, Charles Tamlin Hall Jr. was an active member
13 of First Baptist Church on the Square, where he served as a Deacon, Greeter, and Usher for
