14 over three decades and participated in the Friday Morning Bible Study Group, which he
15 attended for 45 years; and
16 WHEREAS, he was united in love and marriage to his wife, Jan, and was blessed with two
17 remarkable children, Emily and Tamlin, as well as six wonderful grandchildren, Bethany,
18 Hannah, Conner, Addison, Brock, and Hendrix; and
19 WHEREAS, he gave inspiration to many through his high ideals, morals, and deep concern
20 for his fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding he demonstrated to his
21 family and friends were admired by others; and
22 WHEREAS, he was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
23 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example he made of his life, he
24 made this world a better place in which to live; and
25 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Charles Tamlin Hall Jr. will long be
26 remembered for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
27 had the great fortune of knowing him.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
29 join in honoring the life and memory of Charles Tamlin Hall Jr. and express their deepest and
30 most sincere regret at his passing.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
32 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the family of
33 Charles Tamlin Hall Jr.
